<TITLE> Falu's wife faces arrest order for tax dodge </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 5 (bdnews24.com) -- A Dhaka court Thursday issued a warrant to arrest former lawmaker Mosaddek Ali Falu's wife Mahbuba Sultana on charges of tax dodge in a case filed by the National Board of Revenue. Senior special judge Md Azizul Haque for Dhaka issued the warrant after a hearing and set July 11 for submitting a report on implementation of the warrant in presence of the accused. NBR deputy commissioner Md Masudur Rahman Masud filed the case. According to the case details, Mahbuba Sultana, a taxpayer under tax zone 5, furnished false information in her wealth and bank statements for 2001-02 to 2005-06. The NBR claimed that she had concealed earnings of Tk 6.32 crore by providing false information about her furniture, fisheries, house building, investment in shares and fixed deposits. She is accused of dodging Tk 1.58 crore in tax by providing false information. The arrest warrant has been addressed to Falu's permanent address, 797 South Shahjahanpur. In the case, nine people including the complainant have been made witnesses. The case alleged that Mahbuba Sultana had ignored the law despite being a "conscious and respected person". bdnew
